commands.fzmm.item.withoutNbt: That item does not have NBT
fzmm.gui.configGui.colors.comment.imaget: Color used in the description of Imagetext hologram

Color of the resolution message of the Imagetext
and of the name when using the hotkey to generate it
fzmm.gui.configGui.colors.comment.itemFr:
Color used in the description of the items when using
the hotkey to get the item in an item frame
fzmm.gui.configGui.colors.comment.lorePi:
Color of the lore of the item you get when using ctrl+copy or alt+copy

Note: copy defaults to the mouse wheel
fzmm.gui.configGui.colors.comment.player: Color used in Player Statue item names and descriptions
fzmm.gui.configGui.colors.comment.useful:
Color used in the name and description in the creative
item group Useful block states
fzmm.gui.configGui.generic.comment.defau: Item obtained when using Gradient and having no item in hand
The default text when using Imagetext book tooltip
Item obtained when using Imagetext Lore and having no item in hand
fzmm.gui.configGui.generic.comment.disab: Disable italic when adding a name or lore to an item
fzmm.gui.configGui.generic.comment.force: Makes all item frames that have an item appear invisible
fzmm.gui.configGui.generic.comment.giveC:
Makes it so items obtained using the mod are given client-side

Note: if you open the inventory in creative the item is obtained server-side
fzmm.gui.configGui.generic.comment.mines:
Public key from https://mineskin.org/apikey

It is used to reduce the time when generating skins for
- Player Statue
- Head generator

By activating this the skin you upload will be visible to everyone at https://mineskin.org/gallery

By using the following features you may upload skins
- Player Statue
- Head generator
fzmm.gui.configGui.generic.comment.prese: Preserves the aspect ratio of the original image
fzmm.gui.configGui.hotkeys.comment.copyI: Copy the name of the item you have the cursor on as JSON
Copy the name as JSON of the item you have the cursor on
fzmm.gui.configGui.hotkeys.comment.decre: Decrease the minecraft GUI scale setting
fzmm.gui.configGui.hotkeys.comment.fzmmM: Open the main GUI of the mod
fzmm.gui.configGui.hotkeys.comment.gener: Get a 32x32 Imagetext Lore of what you're looking at
fzmm.gui.configGui.hotkeys.comment.giveI: Get the item your cursor is on in an item frame
fzmm.gui.configGui.hotkeys.comment.incre: Increase the minecraft GUI scale setting
fzmm.gui.configGui.hotkeys.comment.parse:
Pasting on an empty slot gives the item in the command in the clipboard
and if pasted on an item it adds the lore to the item
Note: it may be useful to paste ASCII Art found from the internet
fzmm.gui.converters.comment.array.value:
Array UUID

Each of the 4 values in the array must contain a 32-bit signed integer
fzmm.gui.converters.comment.base64.messa: Message to encode or decode in base64
fzmm.gui.converters.comment.uuid.value:
String UUID

The UUID must contain 32 hexadecimal digits.
Example: 069a79f4-44e9-4726-a5be-fca90e38aaf5
fzmm.gui.encryptbook.comment.author: The author of the book
fzmm.gui.encryptbook.comment.maxMessageL:
Maximum characters for the message

Note: without a texture pack that makes the letters
 smaller the maximum is close to 255
fzmm.gui.encryptbook.comment.paddingChar:
Characters to add to the end of the message
to reach the required numbers of characters
fzmm.gui.encryptbook.comment.seed: The seed is used to decrypt and encrypt the data
fzmm.gui.gradient.comment.brightness:
Brightness is the amount of white or black
mixed in with the color
fzmm.gui.gradient.comment.finalColor: Color of the end of the message
fzmm.gui.gradient.comment.hue:
Hue is a degree on the color wheel from 0 to 1.
0 is red, 0.3333 is green, 0.6666 is blue
fzmm.gui.gradient.comment.hueStep:
It is the advance between one letter
and another in the hue value.
fzmm.gui.gradient.comment.initialColor: Color of the beginning of the message
fzmm.gui.gradient.comment.message: The text to apply the gradient to
fzmm.gui.gradient.comment.saturation:
Saturation is the intensity, or richness,
of that color
fzmm.gui.gradient.error.messageLength: The message must be greater than 1 characters
fzmm.gui.imagetext.comment.bookMessage: The text you hover over to see the imagetext
fzmm.gui.imagetext.comment.bookMode:
Choose how the imagetext will be added to the book

Add page: add a page at the end with the imagetext
Create book: create a book with only the imagetext
fzmm.gui.imagetext.comment.characters:
Characters that will be used in the imagetext,
this message will be repeated each time it ends until the line is completed
 and it will have the color of the pixel where it is located

Note: Leaving the default character will replace
 all #000000 with spaces to simulate transparency
fzmm.gui.imagetext.comment.hologramCoord: Coordinates where the hologram is going to be located
fzmm.gui.imagetext.comment.image:
Image used for Imagetext
Tip: Take a screenshot, upload it to imgur URL: Uses the image from that url
Supports: PNG, JPG, GIF (first frame) and BMP

URL: Get the image from that url
Path: Get the image of the path on your pc
fzmm.gui.imagetext.comment.loreMode:
Choose how the imagetext will be added to the item's lore

Add: add the imagetext to the end of existing lores
Set: override lore with imagetext
fzmm.gui.imagetext.comment.resolution: Resolution to which the image will be resized
fzmm.gui.imagetext.comment.smoothImage: Image rescaling type, affects how the imagetext looks
fzmm.gui.option.image.pathDoesNotHaveAFi: The path does not have a file
fzmm.gui.option.skin.name: Name
fzmm.gui.playerStatue.comment.coordinate: Coordinates where the statue will be located
fzmm.gui.playerStatue.comment.skin:
Skin that the statue will have

Name: Username of a premium account
Path: Path of the image on your pc (supports 128x128!)
fzmm.gui.playerStatue.comment.statueName:
The name of the statue, supports JSON format

(Optional)
fzmm.gui.playerStatue.status.error: Statue part error: %s | %s seconds of delay | %s left
fzmm.gui.playerStatue.status.generated: Statue part generated: %s | %s seconds of delay | %s left
